16/08/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski said on Monday (15 August) that he expects 60 per cent of all scheduled sector reforms to be completed by the end of this year. Speaking on national radio, Manasievski repeated that Macedonia -- along with Albania and Croatia -- expects an invitation to join NATO during the Alliance's next summit. One of the most important reforms, the transfer of border control responsibilities from the army to the police, is to be completed by the end of August. (Macedonian Radio - 15/08/05)
